DataElement.preferredDefinition: The original number of specimens available for submission.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._The act of referring for judgment or consideration by others; the act of handing over something._Preceding all others in time or being as first made or performed._A numeral or string of numerals expressing value, quantity, or identification._The quality of being obtainable or accessible and ready for use or service.
